disturbing, psychopathic,

01:04:02.020 --> 01:04:06.540
serial killer fashion have
either an injury or something

01:04:06.540 --> 01:04:11.310
like that, that makes them
predisposed to being very

01:04:11.310 --> 01:04:12.810
inhumane in the way they
think about people.

01:04:15.480 --> 01:04:18.010
And just in case you, as careful
MIT scientists, worry

01:04:18.010 --> 01:04:20.210
about well, maybe they're not
having a GSR that works at

01:04:20.210 --> 01:04:22.220
all, what does that mean?

01:04:22.220 --> 01:04:25.720
If these patients who had the
damage early in childhood just

01:04:25.720 --> 01:04:30.780
get a loud tone, a big boat
horn, like ooh, there's a

01:04:30.780 --> 01:04:32.620
galvanic skin response that
looks pretty good.

01:04:32.620 --> 01:04:35.880
So it's not their autonomic
system won't respond to

01:04:35.880 --> 01:04:38.430
emotionally provocative things,
like a big sound.

01:04:38.430 --> 01:04:40.980
It just doesn't respond to
emotionally provocative things

01:04:40.980 --> 01:04:44.600
like risk and people you
should care about.

01:04:48.250 --> 01:04:49.810
And I'll just end in
this one minute.

01:04:49.810 --> 01:04:54.650
So this is an area where a
guy, Kent Khiel, at the

01:04:54.650 --> 01:04:55.350
University of New Mexico.

01:04:55.350 --> 01:04:56.150
You can go look this up.

01:04:56.150 --> 01:04:57.850
It's an amazing story.

01:04:57.850 --> 01:05:01.830
He's very interested in these
brain differences in

01:05:01.830 --> 01:05:02.640
psychopaths in prison.

01:05:02.640 --> 01:05:05.280
Many are in prison because
they're scary people.

01:05:05.280 --> 01:05:07.150
So you can't get them out to
do research very easily.

01:05:07.150 --> 01:05:09.070
So he has a truck with
an MR scanner.

01:05:09.070 --> 01:05:12.030
And he drives from penitentiary
to penitentiary

01:05:12.030 --> 01:05:14.240
and does brain scanning
with these people.

01:05:14.240 --> 01:05:16.650
And is getting on average,
some differences

01:05:16.650 --> 01:05:18.480
in this brain region.

01:05:18.480 --> 01:05:22.600
So I have a question for you,
just for one minute.

01:05:22.600 --> 01:05:24.935
Do you think that should be
introduced in a court case for

01:05:24.935 --> 01:05:26.185
a serial killer?

01:05:30.840 --> 01:05:34.510
If he gets up there and shows
you brain pictures, should a

01:05:34.510 --> 01:05:38.550
jury hear about that or should
they not hear about that, for

01:05:38.550 --> 01:05:41.416
somebody who's done an
awful murder or an

01:05:41.416 --> 01:05:42.060
awful string murders?

01:05:42.060 --> 01:05:43.330
AUDIENCE: I'd say no.

01:05:43.330 --> 01:05:44.430
PROFESSOR: Sorry.

01:05:44.430 --> 01:05:45.000
You say no.

01:05:45.000 --> 01:05:45.695
Because what?

01:05:45.695 --> 01:05:49.102
AUDIENCE: I think that the risk
is too great that you

01:05:49.102 --> 01:05:51.587
will have innocent
people be shown.

01:05:51.587 --> 01:05:54.072
And the science is not fully
resolved yet in that respect.

01:05:54.072 --> 01:05:56.805
There are also a lot of
salient factors and

01:05:56.805 --> 01:05:59.539
environmental factors that
have been constrained by

01:05:59.539 --> 01:06:03.515
genetics, and say, oh, if you
have this huge issue, this

01:06:03.515 --> 01:06:07.550
condition of the brain, you're
automatically [INAUDIBLE].

01:06:07.550 --> 01:06:08.260
PROFESSOR: OK.

01:06:08.260 --> 01:06:09.330
Let me tell one sentence.

01:06:09.330 --> 01:06:10.230
Yeah, go ahead.

01:06:10.230 --> 01:06:13.530
AUDIENCE: You know the
correlation in one direction--

01:06:13.530 --> 01:06:15.780
PROFESSOR: We don't know.

01:06:15.780 --> 01:06:16.430
These are good points.

01:06:16.430 --> 01:06:18.480
Let me just say, so here's where
we stand now, because

01:06:18.480 --> 01:06:20.320
this will be your lives in
the future, in a lot

01:06:20.320 --> 01:06:21.940
of different ways.

01:06:21.940 --> 01:06:25.580
Where we stand now is, for the
first time ever, brain imaging

01:06:25.580 --> 01:06:29.180
evidence was introduced in the
court case about a year ago of

01:06:29.180 --> 01:06:31.300
a serial killer.

01:06:31.300 --> 01:06:33.120
They were only allowed
to do it--

01:06:33.120 --> 01:06:34.820
court cases like this go
through two phases.

01:06:34.820 --> 01:06:36.520
You see these in TV
shows or movies.

01:06:36.520 --> 01:06:38.300
There's the initial trial.

01:06:38.300 --> 01:06:40.440
And if the person is found
guilty, there's a second phase

01:06:40.440 --> 01:06:42.280
where they decide what the
appropriate penalty is.

01:06:42.280 --> 01:06:46.520
The judge said they could only
be reported in the penalty

01:06:46.520 --> 01:06:48.350
phase, when people were thinking
about what's the

01:06:48.350 --> 01:06:51.610
right punishment for a person,
not before the conviction.

01:06:51.610 --> 01:06:54.640
And they said they couldn't
show any color pictures of

01:06:54.640 --> 01:06:55.660
brain stuff, because that would

01:06:55.660 --> 01:06:58.510
over-influence the jurors.

01:06:58.510 --> 01:07:00.330
And so you could only talk
about this stuff.

01:07:00.330 --> 01:07:02.040
Because if you showed a brain
picture, sort of like you

01:07:02.040 --> 01:07:04.600
said, it would look so
scientific that they were

01:07:04.600 --> 01:07:08.330
afraid it overwhelm the
jurors' judgment.

01:07:08.330 --> 01:07:11.690
So this is all coming up, about
what the brain maybe do

01:07:11.690 --> 01:07:12.570
in your lifetimes.

01:07:12.570 --> 01:07:13.820
Thanks.

